                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.13/8.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 7, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>President Gomez to-day signed the amnesty bill in spite of having full knowledge
                    of the views of Department’s March 7, and of the threatened American
                    interests.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
